Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @tomato{1}. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Halve and peel @onion{1}; thinly slice one half. Finely chop remaining onion until you have 2 TBSP. Quarter @lime{1}. Halve, core, and thinly slice @green bell pepper{1} into strips.

== Tomato Salsa ==

In a #medium bowl{}, combine tomato, cilantro, chopped onion, juice from half the lime, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch}.

== Hot Sauce Crema ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{3%tablespoon} with as much @hot sauce{1%teaspoon} as you like. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt.

== Filling ==

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{}, @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}, @chili powder{1%teaspoon}, and a few big pinches of salt. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned, ~{4-5%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in the next step).

Once beef is browned, add bell pepper, sliced onion, and a pinch of salt to pan. Cook, stirring, until veggies are tender and beef is cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Add @beef stock concentrate{1} and 1/4 cup water (1/2 cup water for 4 servings). Simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt; remove pan from heat and set aside.

== Tostadas ==

Drizzle @flour tortillas{6} with @olive oil{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings); brush or rub to coat all over. Arrange on a #baking sheet{} in a single layer (divide between two sheets for 4). Gently prick each tortilla in a few places with a #fork{}.

Bake on top rack, flipping halfway through, until lightly golden, ~{4-5%minutes} per side. (For 4, bake on top and middle racks; flip tortillas and swap rack positions halfway through baking.)

> Watch carefully—tortillas brown fast!

Divide tortillas between plates; evenly sprinkle with @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup}. Top with beef mixture, salsa, and crema. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.